{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"close-ferreous-cardinal","description":"# Comprehensive live reconciler validation + guaranteed bilateral cleanup\n\n## Why\nThis epic's correctness is argued from the code and an OSS/commercial-tier comparison (session log\nspirited-balsamic-sealion) but never PROVEN end-to-end against live Jira. The store-hardening,\nconvergence, and latent-gap fixes all change live sync behavior. An agent with ACLI access must\nvalidate the full bidirectional surface on a live Jira and GUARANTEE cleanup of every test artifact in\nBOTH systems.\n\n## What\nBuild a live-validation harness (create -> exercise -> assert -> teardown) whose teardown is\nGUARANTEED even on assertion failure/exception, then run a comprehensive matrix:\n- Create -> bind round-trip (outbound create, `rebar-id:` label, `local_id` entity property, JQL dedup).\n- Echo suppression: our own writes (echo-marked comments, status, fields) are NOT re-ingested inbound.\n- Three-way-merge direction: local-edit wins; a Jira-edit with unchanged local mirrors inbound; a true both-sides conflict emits the C1 signal.\n- Status round-trip incl. lossy statuses (blocked/cancelled via `rebar-status:` labels; idea<->IDEA); no oscillation over N passes.\n- Deletion/tombstone: local archive -> Jira Done; Jira 404 -> grace -> reversible retire; snapshot-absence never destroys.\n- Hard-delete -> re-create (C2); field-allowlist-drop alert (C3); bulk-path 429/Retry-After (C4, fault-injected if needed).\n- Idempotency: two consecutive passes on an unchanged remote -> mutation_count = 0.\n- Blast-radius breaker: no trip on a normal pass; trips on a synthetic mass-change.\n\n## Scope & isolation\nPrefer an ISOLATED test scope - a dedicated Jira test project + an isolated local env (see epic\nodd-vortex-elbow) or clearly-labeled throwaway tickets scoped by a test JQL/label - so production REB\nand the shared tickets branch are never polluted. HONEST caveat: local ticket \"deletion\" is a status\nchange; the underlying append-only events persist in git history, so isolate via a throwaway env where\npossible rather than relying on delete.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Live-validation harness with GUARANTEED bilateral teardown (cleanup in a finally/fixture even on failure).\n- [ ] Comprehensive matrix above executed against live Jira; results recorded on the ticket.\n- [ ] ZERO surviving test artifacts after a run: test issues hard-deleted in Jira; test tickets archived/deleted locally; a leaked-artifact sweep runs before AND after.\n- [ ] Isolation approach chosen and documented; production REB untouched.\n- [ ] Re-runnable: a second run leaves both systems in the same clean state (idempotent teardown).\n","id":"d01e-d48d-de62-4833","parent_id":"ace2-f784-4b19-4f22","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Comprehensive live reconciler validation + guaranteed bilateral cleanup"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783471713313748001,"uuid":"51b28a53-57a8-43f2-9ba1-6bfdf2e91227"}